articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Icelandic authorities have completed the evacuation of 3,000 residents of a town in the southwestern part of the country over concerns of a volcanic eruption after a series of earthquakes and evidence of magma spreading underground.
articles.title: Iceland evacuates town over concerns of volcanic eruption

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Members of a group of relatives of victims of enforced disappearances in Turkey held a vigil on Saturday in central Istanbul without police intervention for the first time since 2018.
articles.title: Turkey allows decades-old mothers' vigil after five-year ban

articles.author: David Morgan
articles.description: U.S. House of Representatives Republicans are due to unveil a stopgap measure on Saturday aimed at averting a government shutdown, the latest in a series of standoffs that contributed to Moody's lowering its outlook on the nation's credit.
articles.title: House Republicans eye plan to avert government shutdown

articles.author: David Alire Garcia
articles.description: Mexico's ruling party on Saturday picked veteran politician Clara Brugada to be its candidate for Mexico City mayor, placing her in a strong position to win the election next June.
articles.title: Mexico's ruling party again picks woman to run for mayor of capital

articles.author: Rupam Jain
articles.description: Three Bangladeshi tourists died in India's Kashmir region when some of the houseboats stationed in the picturesque Dal lake caught fire on Saturday, a police official said.
articles.title: Three Bangladeshi tourists die in houseboat fire in India's Kashmir

articles.author: Raphael Satter
articles.description: Private spy firm Black Cube was behind a hidden video campaign that used LinkedIn to target Hungarian activists and journalists leading to last year's election in the central European country, the professional networking site said on Thursday.
articles.title: LinkedIn says spy firm targeted Hungarian activists, journalists before 2022 election

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Australian government said on Saturday that it was coordinating a response to a cybersecurity incident that forced ports operator DP World Australia to suspend operations at ports in several states.
articles.title: Australia ports operator suffers 'cybersecurity incident', suspends operations

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Israel faced mounting international pressure, including from its main ally the United States, to do more to protect Palestinian civilians in Gaza as the death toll rose and fighting intensified between Israeli forces and Hamas militants near and around hospitals.
articles.title: As Gaza death toll rises, Israel faces pressure to protect Palestinian civilians

articles.author: Patrick Wingrove
articles.description: Novo Nordisk (NOVOb.CO) on Saturday said the heart protective benefits of its wildly popular Wegovy obesity treatment are due to more than weight loss alone, according to new data presented at a major medical meeting on Saturday.
articles.title: Novo Nordisk says Wegovy heart benefits due to more than weight loss

articles.description: Follow on Apple, Google or Spotify. Listen on the Reuters app. Read the episode transcript.
articles.title: Listen Now: SpaceX employees say they’re paying the price for Musk’s push to colonize Mars
